  "doc_id": "4526",
  "text": "FM IL-1b secretion in response to viral ssRNA is caspase-1 dependent Since viral ssRNA, but not Poly(I:C), induced the FMs to produce IL-1b, we further examined the mechanism involved. We previously demonstrated that human FMs express the inflammasome components Nalp1, Nalp3, ASC (apoptosis-associated speck-like protein containing a CARD) and caspase-1 [CITATION_1] , which mediate the processing of intracellular pro-IL-1b into its active, secreted form [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In the presence of a caspase-1 inhibitor, IL-1b secretion induced by viral ssRNA was significantly reduced by 54.7% (Fig. 3) .",
